docs.snippet: The record-setting $485 million renovation of Texas A&M’s home stadium, Kyle Field, is the story of a university that found itself with more money than it knew what to do with....
docs.lead_paragraph: The record-setting $485 million renovation of Texas A&M’s home stadium, Kyle Field, is the story of a university that found itself with more money than it knew what to do with.
docs.abstract: Texas A&M football stadium Kyle Field, now fourth largest stadium in college football, continues to sell out every home game; record-setting $485 million renovation increased its capacity from 82,600 to 102,733, and its features include 12 Founders Club suites, Hall of Champions as well as 12th Man Studios for broadcasting.

headline.main: In Southeastern Conference, Nothing’s Bigger Than Texas A&M’s Field
headline.print_headline: Texas A&M’s Field Is Now as Big as Its Ambitions

docs.abstract: Tyler Kepner On Baseball column says that Chicago Cubs, busy preparing for National League Championship Series, have most imposing young lineup in Major League Baseball; notes that Cubs, led by players mostly in their 20s, won their last eight games of regular season and now have won four of five in playoffs.

headline.main: Fortunately for Cubs, Their Young Stars Are Making Their Own History
headline.print_headline: Cubs, Full of Power and Promise, Shrug Off History’s Burden
